To convert a JSON string `{"price":"2020.53","volume":"258669.98","lastMarket":"CCCAGG"}` to a struct in Solidity, you can define a struct with the same structure as the JSON object and use the `abi.decode` function to parse the JSON string into an instance of the struct.

